
Ask AI the following.

Help me write a future letter to myself, starting with:

Dear Vivek,

Its amazing how far you have come as you have studied AI.
Here's what I have created, who I have becomen, what I have unlocked, and what I have let go of.

Here is the Output.

Dear Vivek,

It’s amazing how far you have come as you have studied AI.

Here’s what I have created:
I have built systems that don’t just process data, but solve human problems. Whether it was my first neural network or the sophisticated open-source projects I contribute to today, I have moved from consuming technology to architecting it.

Who I have become:
I am no longer someone intimidated by the speed of change. I have become a lifelong student with a "beta mindset"—always updating, always refining. I’ve balanced my technical depth with an ethical compass, ensuring that everything I build serves a greater purpose.

What I have unlocked:
I have unlocked a new way of thinking. Studying AI has sharpened my logic and expanded my creativity, allowing me to use LLMs and generative tools as an extension of my own mind. I’ve unlocked the freedom to focus on high-level strategy because I’ve mastered the automation of the mundane.

What I have let go of:
I have let go of the fear of being replaced. I’ve realized that AI is a tool, not a rival. I’ve also let go of the need to know everything at once; I now trust my ability to learn what I need when the time comes. Most importantly, I’ve let go of perfectionism, choosing instead the power of iterative progress.

Keep pushing forward,
Vivek


